radiographic_examinations.findings: A 6 × 4 × 4 cm right adnexal mass complicated by right ovarian torsion with pre-operative rupture; an 8.8 × 6.6 × 9.3 cm pelvic mass, omental and peritoneal metastases, complex ascites, small pericardial and bilateral pleural effusions; a large left frontal mass with midline shift.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Approximately 6 months prior to this presentation, the patient had undergone a right salpingo-oophorectomy and peritoneal mass resection at another institution.
